<br>
While a contract will be voided for lack of consideration, it is very rare for a court to evaluate whether the consideration seems to be &quot;equal&quot; or &quot;fair.&quot;  Here, EZBoard can argue that when the money is paid for the future use of the servers, there is sufficient consideration simply by virtue of EZBoard's making the space and services available even if you chose not to use them.<br>
<br>
It is kind of like a magazine subscition.  You can enter into a contract where you agree to pay X dollars for 12 issues, and (unless there is a cancellation policy) if you decide you do not like it you still cannot just bail on the agreement and say you want your money back.  Sometimes it helps to look at what you bought:  were you buying services month by month, or were you buying a block of months' worth of services.  There is a difference, just like there is a difference between having a month to month lease, and signing a year long lease.<br>
<br>
